Create a Launch template
--------------------------
Creating a launch template allow you to create a saved launch configuration 
that can be reused ,shared and launched at a later time. Templates can have 
multiple verison 

Step that will be followed while creating and Instance :

Launch template  name and description 
Step 1: Launch template name 
Step 2: Template version description 
Step 3: If you want you can select Auto Scaling Guidance option 

Step 4: Add the template tag to apply it to the launch template
Step 5: You can optionally specify a source template if you would like to 
        create  a template from another existing template 

Launch tmeplate contents:
Specify the details of your launch template below : Leaving a filed blank 
will result in the filed  not being  included in the launch template 

Step 6: Application and OS image
        \_Recents - Don't include in Launch template
                  \_Recently launched 
        \_My_AMI -Don't include in the launch template
                 \_ Owned by me 
                 \_Shared with me 
        \_Quick Start [ here no AMI  or refferences you create a new one ]
Step 6: Instance type
Step 7: Key_Pair
Step 8: Networking settings
Step 9: Storage 
Step 10: Resource Tag
Step 11: Specify the Additinal details 

[ From the step 6 to step 11 it's same as   Ec2 but according to your 
configuration ]


